_sText: So this is my 3rd real map and ends the trilogy of CS Source maps i have created. Everything in this, like on my other maps too, have been done from scratch. I have not edited any existing maps or anything, this is all from my own head. So In this map, i wanted to try out another scenario. 1 close bombsite and 1 more far away. Its all about the teamwork which team will win. There are enough routes to avoid bottleneck fights and it is fully balanced for both teams! This map is on cycle at server: 89.166.50.111:27025 I created this during 2 months of time. This is the best optimized map i have done since the start to the end. It compiles on normal only in 19 minutes which i consider a good result! I left HDR off because it cutted -100fps off straight on, even if i really tried to optimize it to the map. It did that even if it wouldnt be on at players PC but the map had support for HDR. Weird stuff, i know but map looks fine without it too! Playability over eyecandy, thats my motto. Check out all my other maps from http://www.ics-base.net/css_maps

"Well de_tegea_s is on the verge of completion…

This map was originally made for CS 1.6 by a mapper named “3D Punk”.
My friends and I were big fans of the map
and after trying to contact the mapper with no luck, I chose to rebuild the map myself for CS Source with a few additions
which I felt made the maps game play a bit more even.

The map is completed.
Latest updates to the map to make it final.

1. The NPC characters have been removed to improve on frame rates
as well as fix nav mesh issues.
2. Clipped some rocks in one stairwell to avoid players from
getting stuck.
3. Added some new lighting to the map mainly in two dark areas that
would have been camper's paradise.
4. Added nav file for bot play
5. Added working soundscape
6. All files are embedded and fully working."

DE_TEGEA_CSS_FINAL in essence it's a capital re-build of the prerevious version this map named [DE_TEGEA_S](http://css.gamebanana.com/maps/17179) (known also under the name DE_TEGEA_FINAL) released October 2006. It was an first author's remake of popular map for classical Counter-Strike [DE_TEGEA](http://cs.gamebanana.com/maps/157794) by 3DPunk (released December 2001).

DE_TEGEA_CSS_FINAL was released May 2007, and included a set of changes (redesigned, added or deleted some locations) and improvements (overall textures and lightnings replacements) in comparison with the previous version.

DE_TEGEA_CSS_FINAL is an office-styled map which for 80% consists of indoor locations, and also is very friendly for intense closed fights and stealth actions.

GENERAL CREDITS & GRATITUDES:
3DPunk (for very popular release for classic CS),
MayheM (for beautyful office/industrial themed remake for CS:S),
BarnDoor (for good playable navigation meshes for many fine CS:S maps).

Play and Enjoy :-)

- - - - - - - - - - - -

**ABOUT PLAYING WITH BOTS:**

In archive with the original map included the more or less playable .nav-file (Navigation Mesh for playing with Bots) optimized by [Peter 'BarnDoor' Calvert](http://www.tequilakawa.plus.com/) for use on public and private servers. "This nav was placepainted already, I assume by the map author, and I've maintained this. Nearly all the ladders didn't work, and one of the main routes from TSpawn wasn't connected, so there is a significant difference in bot behaviour on this edit." Still quite recently it was the best of all available nav-files for this map, but it was not perfect playable :-(

Therefore [**here**](http://css.gamebanana.com/gamefiles/3488) is available for downloading a manually optimized and fully place painted NAV-file for this Great map!

studio@sixdimensional.com

Map Description:
This map is based on a fictional area and scenario. The textures have been taken from the raw files provided in Counter-Strike Source. This map is set in a foggy night-time atmosphere.
This map trains stealth and quick mindedness by testing players' abilities to plan an assault on an area. Both the Counter-Terrorists and Terrorists begin beyond the bombsites, however the terrorists are able to get to the bombsites quicker, depicting a realistic scenario where the terrorists arrive at the scene first. The Terrorists begin in a storage chamber which is linked to a ventilation system. This can be used as access to the bombsites. The Counter-Terrorists have to storm the area though a chokepoint, which is surrounded by trees, to give cover.
The bombsites are the warehouse and the sentry-house.

The bombsites:
1) The sentry-house is a key communication centre in the map. If the terrorists take this out then the factory-warehouse will no longer be able to ship off weapons where needed. This will lead to an immediate win for the terrorists regardless of survival.
2) The warehouse is an obvious target for the terrorists. With the chamber full of explosives, a major spark will set off the entire warehouse, and create local chaos, as well as banishing weapons for the Counter-Terrorists.

As with any "de_" map, the terrorists are the ones with the explosives, the the counter-terrorists are out to stop them.

There is a limited amount of bot support on this map, the Terrorist bots are less able to roam around the vents and will most likely remain at spawn, but the Counter-Terrorist bots are more able to move about the map. Please stay tuned for updates with this feature.
Secondly, the lift to the "right" is slightly glitchy when activated, however this should not affect your playability unless you use the "trap-door". This is being worked on.

TO INSTALL:
1) Put the map into your:
%dir%/Valve/Steam/SteamApps/Username/counter-strike source/map
folder

Pretty small and fast paced gameplay. Nav included for convenience, load it up and test. There are quite a few options with gameplay, several pathway connections allow for the other team to 'sneak up' on you planting the bomb/defending the bombsite, although a few places may be seen as 'campsites' they are generally pretty useless and defenceless...allowing for the fast gameplay. Background A historical site surrounded by modernised housing has been targeted by environmental terrorists. As time progressed, the area has become much more modern, hence the swimming pool etc... It's a small map with a "fast and furious" gameplay.

In a heavy snowstorm a plane carrying a topsecret load gets in trouble. The onboard guard parachute to safety. They recover the crashed plane and start unloading the cargo into a cargo area. But the weather plays a second trick as heavy snowfall prevent the SWAT-team from getting the entire cargo over to the cargo area. Terrorist have tracked the plane as well and in an attempt to prevent the Swat-Team from escaping with their valuable load they set a plan to bomb the two possible locations of the load.
